  "text": "Concerning PET-CT, the most commonly used and widely available radiotracer is 18 F-FDG that is a non-specific tumor-seeking radiopharmaceutical. PSMA [CITATION_1] . In a retrospective analysis of 319 patients who underwent Ga-PSMA-ligand PET-CT, the same team found that PSMA is highly specific for PCa and detects the disease in a high percentage of patients (82.8%) [CITATION_2] . All of the methods mentioned above are irradiating and require the injection of contrast material or radioactive tracers.",
